  "prompt": "What universities does Concert Pharmaceuticals recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Concert Pharmaceuticals, like many biotechnology and pharmaceutical companies, typically recruits new graduates from universities with strong programs in relevant fields. While I can't provide a specific list of universities they recruit from, candidates often come from institutions known for their life sciences, chemistry, biology, biochemistry, pharmaceutical sciences, or related disciplines.\n\nIn terms of majors, Concert Pharmaceuticals usually looks for graduates with degrees in:\n\n- Biology\n- Biochemistry\n- Chemistry\n- Pharmaceutical Sciences\n- Biomedical Engineering\n- Molecular Biology\n- Related life sciences fields\n\nIf you're interested in opportunities at Concert Pharmaceuticals, it\u2019s a good idea to check their careers page or LinkedIn for specific job postings and requirements, as they will provide the most accurate and updated information on the roles they are hiring for. Networking through career fairs and university alumni connections can also be helpful.",
